<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.J.28.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Article 21, paragraph 8</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>At the end of Article 21 add a new paragraph 8, worded as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>8. “<hi rend="italic">Any instrument drawn up or contract
                                        concluded during the war on occupied territory between Greek
                                        and Bulgarian nationals, purporting to transfer Greek
                                        property, subsequently removed to Bulgaria, shall be null
                                        and void</hi>.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>